## Layer responsibilities (Clean Architecture)

| Layer | Path | Agent rule |
|-------|------|------------|
| Domain | `domain/services`, `domain/aggregates`, `domain/events`, **`domain/ports/`** | Business rules; persistence via ports; no tRPC/api-v1 imports |
| Application | **`application/use-cases/`** (~60) | Orchestration; no `@InjectModel` / `@nestjs/mongoose` / `trpc/*` |
| Adapters | **`adapters/`** + legacy `trpc/`, `api-v1/` | Thin transport ‚Üí use case ‚Üí map ‚Üí `ResourcePermissions` |
| Infrastructure | **`infrastructure/persistence/`**, `infrastructure/auth`, `infrastructure/cron`, `infrastructure/telegram` | Implements ports; Mongoose here only |

See @architecture.mdc **Remaining debt** for Tier-3 `@InjectModel` scripts and OD-3.

## Module Wiring Rule
- Use a shared `domain.module.ts` for providers and model registration.
- Do not assume "one module per entity" layout.
- **New orchestration:** add `application/use-cases/[domain]/[action].use-case.ts`; router calls `createXUseCase(ctx).execute(...)`.
- **Do not** add cross-router imports (ESLint Zone 9).

## API Layer Responsibilities

### tRPC (`trpc/routers` ‚Üí target `adapters/trpc/routers`)
- Validate input with shared Zod schemas when possible.
- **Target:** thin controllers ‚Äî delegate to application use cases; map via `EntityMappers`; attach permissions via engine + presenter.
- **Do not** import logic from other routers (Zone 9).
- No new REST business endpoints; dual transport = tRPC primary + REST auth narrow.
- tRPC procedures use shared middleware for Sentry profiling and `HttpException` -> `TRPCError` mapping (`trpc/trpc.ts`).
- Current router groups: `users`, `communities`, `auth`, `config`, `publications`, `comments`, `votes`, `polls`, `wallets`, `notifications`, `search`, `uploads`, `favorites`, `categories`, `about`, `tappalka`, `investments`, `teams`, `platformSettings`, `project`, `ticket`, `platformDev`, `meritTransfer`.
- Investments group is mounted as `investments` in appRouter, with implementation file `trpc/routers/investment.router.ts`.
- Platform dev group is mounted as `platformDev` in appRouter, with implementation file `trpc/routers/platform-dev.router.ts` (superadmin-only procedures).

### REST (`api-v1`)
- Used for selected flows (auth/providers, config, passkeys/WebAuthn, SMS OTP, email magic link, phone call-check, magic-link redeem), plus development/test auth endpoints (`fake`, `fake/superadmin`, `mock/:provider`), with shared REST helpers/services under `api-v1/common`.
- Upload REST endpoints are kept for backward compatibility and marked deprecated; prefer tRPC uploads endpoints for new code. Note: permission parity is not complete - `api-v1/uploads/community/:communityId/avatar` currently has a TODO for lead-role enforcement, while tRPC checks lead/superadmin.
- Reuse domain services and shared helpers where possible; current REST/tRPC layers also use dedicated enrichment/mapping helpers from `api-v1/common`.

## Bootstrap and Runtime Wiring
- `main.ts` mounts tRPC via Express middleware (`/trpc`) before Nest routes to correctly handle batched requests.
- Cookie parser is mounted on the raw Express app before tRPC middleware so authenticated and batched `/trpc` requests have parsed cookies in context.
- `main.ts` also calls `app.use(cookieParser())` again later (after tRPC setup); the file notes this mount is redundant but safe.
- Global exception/response handling is configured in bootstrap (`ApiExceptionFilter`, `ApiResponseInterceptor`).
- Sentry is initialized during bootstrap and also used in tRPC procedure middleware.

## Permission Flow

1. Route/middleware resolves actor and target context (`permission.middleware.ts`).
2. **`PermissionRuleEngine.canPerformAction`** ‚Äî role √ó action from `permissionRules` (live).
3. **Post-type / product gates** ‚Äî target: engine methods via **`PermissionGatesPort`** (Phase 3 stubs ‚Üí Phase 5 inlined logic). **Interim:** gates live in `permissions-helper.service.ts` (V-06); engine must **not** import permissions-helper.
4. **`permissions.presenter`** (target Phase 5) ‚Äî `ResourcePermissions` booleans + i18n disabled-reason keys only; no gate logic in presenter.
5. Domain services enforce wallet/quota/source rules (`CreateVoteUseCase` target).
6. Permission checks **before** side effects (inv-08).
7. Notifications via domain event ‚Üí **`NotificationHandlersService`** (not inline `createNotification` in domain ‚Äî V-05 waiver on `ob_vote_join_offer` until Phase 5).

**Nest DI (Phase 3):** `PermissionGatesPort` token ‚Üí `PermissionGatesAdapter` in `infrastructure/permissions/permissions.module.ts`; adapter is sole infra importer of `permissions-helper`. Engine injects port via `@Inject(PermissionGatesPort)`.

**OD-3 sign-off:** product signatures on `.index/architecture/od3-matrix-signed.yaml` required before Phase 5 permissions migration merge.

Never rely on UI assumptions for security-critical checks.

### Auth Implementation Notes (Current Code)
- OAuth-related flows use the REST auth controller and Passport strategies (`api-v1/auth/strategies/google.strategy.ts`, `api-v1/auth/strategies/mailru.strategy.ts`); Yandex OAuth routes and callbacks are in `api-v1/auth/auth.controller.ts`.
- Passkeys support both split flows (`register/login`) and unified flow (`passkey/authenticate/start|finish`).
- Magic-link redeem endpoint includes in-memory IP rate limiting.
- Legacy `GET /api/v1/auth/me` exists and is marked deprecated in favor of `trpc.users.getMe`.

## Data and Schema Rules
- Shared API contracts: `libs/shared-types/src/` ‚Äî canonical for cross-stack DTOs (inv-12).
- **`ResourcePermissionsSchema`** in `schemas.ts` is source of truth; Phase 1 deletes `api-v1/common/interfaces/resource-permissions.interface.ts`.
- Domain imports from shared-types: **allowlist only** (value-objects, taxonomy, value-rubricator, decree809-tag-remap) ‚Äî not full `schemas.ts` (zone 6).
- Phase 1 stub: export `NotificationRoutingSchema` from `schemas.ts` (no backend runtime dependency yet).
- Backend-only schemas: `api/apps/meriter/src/common/schemas/` (e.g. `pagination.schema.ts` ‚Äî canonical pagination; replace inline router pagination in Phase 1).
- Most Mongoose models are in `domain/models/**`; additional schemas can also exist in dedicated feature modules (e.g. `updates-conductors/model`).
- Auth persistence schemas are in `domain/models/auth/**` (`passkey-challenge.schema.ts`, `auth-magic-link.schema.ts`, `sms-otp.schema.ts`). Email login has no OTP collection ‚Äî it uses `auth-magic-link` records only.
- When changing contract shape, update both backend usage and frontend consumers.

## Service Pattern

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class ExampleService {
  constructor(
    @InjectModel(ExampleSchemaClass.name)
    private readonly exampleModel: Model<ExampleDocument>,
  ) {}

  async execute(input: Input): Promise<Output> {
    // business logic, validation, persistence
  }
}
```

## Router Pattern

```typescript
export const exampleRouter = router({
  create: protectedProcedure
    .input(CreateExampleSchema)
    .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      return ctx.exampleService.execute(input);
    }),
});
```

## Stub procedures (resolved)

- `wallets.withdraw` / `wallets.transfer` ‚Äî **permanent NOT_IMPLEMENTED**; rating withdrawal = `publications.withdraw`; peer transfer = `meritTransfer.*`; hide UI callers (Phase 1 grep).

## ESLint boundaries (**landed**)

Zones 1‚Äì9 enforced in `api/.eslintrc.js` (see @architecture.mdc). New code must not violate layer imports.

## Common Mistakes

‚ùå Putting business rules directly in tRPC routers/controllers (extract to use cases per phase plan)
‚ùå `PermissionRuleEngine` importing `permissions-helper` ‚Äî use `PermissionGatesPort`
‚ùå Domain service importing `trpc/helpers` (V-01) or reading `process.env` for feature flags (V-07)
‚ùå Cross-router imports (Zone 9)
‚ùå Inline notification creation in domain services (OD-12 / V-05)
‚ùå Duplicating validation instead of reusing shared schemas
‚ùå Skipping permission checks for "internal" endpoints
‚ùå Mixing REST/tRPC contracts without explicit mapping (inv-18: envelopes stay distinct)
‚ùå Applying tRPC permission middleware before `.input()` validation when resource IDs are extracted from input
‚ùå Treating deprecated REST upload endpoints as the primary API surface (OD-2 audit Phase 6b)
‚ùå Introducing backend-only DTOs into shared-types without cross-package need
‚ùå Assuming deprecated REST endpoints enforce the same permission checks as their tRPC replacements
‚ùå Adding `@nestjs/mongoose` imports in `application/**` (zone 5)
